    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn command mode, when you input a number greater than 1, then join lines with `J`, I find that the command is repeated one less time than it should.\n\nWhen inputting for example `2J` (see example below), maybe the output is supposed to tell me that nvim is \"joining 2 lines\" (hence the behavior from inputting only 1 `J` command), but isn't this inconsistent with how `2X` should execute `X` twice?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSorry for not making this very formal, I'm not that good at configuring vim.\nThis runs with vanilla nvim with no plugins (`sudo nvim` or `nvim -u DEFAULTS`), please tell me if this is unclear and I will edit the issue.\n\nIn normal mode:\n\n[before]\n```\n|foo\nbar\nbaz\n```\n(`|` indicates the cursor position, not using images for accessibility)\n\n[command] `2J`\n\n[after]\n```\nfoo |bar\nbaz\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFor the above example, I am expecting to see this output:\n\n[before]\n```\n|foo\nbar\nbaz\n```\n\n[command] `2J`\n\n[after]\n```\nfoo bar| baz\n```\n\nwhich is the output I get when inputting `3J`.\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.4, LuaJIT 2.1.1713484068\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.1.697\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWSL 2.4.11.0 (same behaviour in Windows 10)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n5.15.167.4-microsoft-standard-WSL2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nsystem package manager",
